<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 EW/12–644: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06">December 6,
                                1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 6—6:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4659. Press for December 6 publish[ed] prominently Lublin account dated
                            December 3 of hanging of five Hitlerites sentenced for crimes committed
                            in Majdanek death camp.</p>
                        <p>Execution was witnessed by over 20,000 persons who according to story,
                            hurled imprecations at Hitlerites, such as “that is what they deserve”.
                            Despatch adds that execution was greeted by stormy approval.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Department as 4659, repeated to London as 285 for Schoenfeld.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>